        <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;how-to-setup-reverse-proxy-with-iis&#34;&gt;How to Setup Reverse proxy with IIS&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I testing it on Server 2016 with IIS 10&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;install-iisurl-_rewrite-arr&#34;&gt;Install IIS,URL _REWRITE, ARR&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install IIS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Download and install &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://www.iis.net/downloads/microsoft/url-rewrite&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;URL Rewrite Module 2.1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Download and install &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://www.iis.net/downloads/microsoft/application-request-routing&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;ARR-Application-request-routing&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;setting-reverse-proxy&#34;&gt;Setting Reverse Proxy&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Select Root level in IIS management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click ‘Application Request Routing Cache’,then in the right side, click “proxy | Server proxy Settings | Check on “Enable proxy” | save config.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Select website in IIS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click URL Rewrite&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add a black Rule&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;* Match URL:
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
